EForge is a Django application, and must be deployed as such. As a large piece
of software, it has a number of dependencies; full information on the
requirements can be found on the project wiki:
    http://eforge.e43.eu/p/eforge/wiki/Requirements

The wiki also contains installation instructions:
    http://eforge.e43.eu/p/eforge/wiki/Installation


Directory tree information:

|
|- eforge           EForge source code root (Python module) & core components
|  \
|  |- browser       Source browser plugin
|  |- bugs          Issue tracker plugin
|  |- utils         Utility functions
|  |- wiki          Wiki plugin
|  |- update        Update notification system
|  |  \
|  |   |- email     E-Mail notification backend plugin
|  |   |- twitter   Twitter notification backend plugin
|  |- vcs           VCS integration plugin
|  |  \
|  |   |- git       Git VCS plugin
|  |   |- hg        Hg VCS plugin
|
|- templates    EForge templates root & EForge overall template
|  \
|  |- TCWiki    Templates for TCWiki (backend of the Wiki plugin)
|  |- bugs      Templates for the issue tracker plugin
|  |- browser   Templates for the source browser plugin
|  |- eforge    Templates for eforge core components pages (e.g. about)
|
|- static       Static files relating to overall look and feel
|  \
|  |- browser   Browser theme files
|  |- images    jQueryUi images
|  |- issues    Issue tracker images (inconsistency: rename to bugs)
|  |- jQuery    jQuery & jQueryUi and themes
|  |- silk      famfamfam silk icons